    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are primed for a high-ceiling Saturday, anchored by **Gunnar Henderson**, who earns our highest daily score of 81.88. Facing Houser, **Henderson** benefits from a massive 16% park factor boost and the optimal leadoff spot, making him a locked-in core play. **Marcell Ozuna** and **Miguel Vargas** also offer significant upside today; **Ozuna** is aided by a 10% wind-out factor in his matchup against Taillon, while **Vargas** leverages a favorable wind and prime leadoff placement to elevate his projection well above his base. Despite the daunting matchup against deGrom, **Kyle Tucker** remains a mandatory start; while his raw output is suppressed by the elite opponent, his order-dependent efficiency keeps him comfortably in the \"Strong\" category.\n\nThe most difficult decision on today\u2019s board involved **Josh Jung**, who narrowly missed the starting cut with a score of 57.90. While his favorable matchup against Sasaki provides a solid 19% boost in SP skill, he was ultimately benched because his lower batting order position (-6%) and the overall strength of our starting infield\u2014specifically **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** and **Jorge Polanco**\u2014offered superior categorical accumulation. Managers should remain cautious regarding the risks posed by **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, whose matchup against a sharp Woodruff (2.90 xERA) highlights our lowest projected starter score (53.67). We are effectively sacrificing some floor in the MI slot today to capitalize on the platoon advantages and power potential found in the rest of the lineup.",
